As Ness closes in on Al Capone, the mysterious Danny Shaw accidentally prevents the lawman from bringing down Scarface once and for all. Can Shaw set things right? description:
As the only remaining boy in the world, Erik Farrell has to piece his memories together, while trying to forge a new life for himself in a patchwork world.

Created by writer David Gallaher and artist Steve Ellis (collaborators since 2007), The Only Living Boy debuted at San Diego Comic Con 2012. The first issue was successfully funded by a Kickstarter campaign in March 2012. Half of the goal total was raised in the first eight days of the campaign, which ran for one month and ended at $4,500 over the target $11,000.

The creators cite Flash Gordon, John Carter, The Jungle Book, and Planet Of The Apes as sources of inspiration.

The digital edition of Issue #1 was available free of charge on Free Comic Book Day 2013. The series was nominated for two 2013 Harvey Awards for Best Inking and Best Cover. In 2014, the series was nominated again for a Harvey Award, this time for Best Graphic Publication for Younger Readers.

On March 26th 2014, the series was released as a free webcomic at: the-only-living-boy.com
name: The Only Living Boy

deck: Featuring Anthony Starks, the Ghostface Killah.
description:
Six-part mini-series based on the hip-hop album of the same name and created by Adrian Younge and Ghostface Killah. The comic is written by Adrian Younge, CE Garcia, Matthew Rosenberg, with illustrations from Breno Tamura (The Lead Years), Gus Storms (The Dead Years) and various other artists contributing flashback scenes and additional splash pages. Produced by Bob Perry, Matt Pizzolo, and the RZA through Black Mask Studios and Soul Temple Entertainment.

The story is set in Italy during the 1960s and 1980s - dubbed The Lead Years and The Dead Years. The Lead Years focus on the mafia clan the 12 DeLucas and their rise to power until they meet Anthony Stark, the Ghostface Killah. The Dead Years follow a record hunter, or "crate digger" as he likes to be called, as he searches for the vinyl records that were played during the death of the DeLucas.
name: 12 Reasons To Die
